summary:
to those complaining about Dan’s absence:
- y’all would apparently “do anything for him”, except show him an ounce of respect
-...
body:
to those complaining about Dan’s absence:

- y’all would apparently “do anything for him”, except show him an ounce of respect

- you dont seem to realise that the shit you chat about him on every social platform you have, Dan can easily see

- branding him as neglectful and careless towards his fanbase while still having him or Phil as your profile pics?

- y’all go back to worshipping him the second he posts anything, as if you werent talkin smack 3 tweets prior

…nice.

I can guarantee that once Dan comes back these people will act like they never talked badly about him, and that’s absolutely disgusting.

to disrespect someone for doing what’s right FOR HIM sounds like an underlying issue you have with depending on others for joy that you expect them to provide you with. Dan has no obligation to churn out content just because you want it, he’s responsible for HIMSELF, not you.

can you imagine how heartbreaking it must be for Dan to see people who supposedly “love” him saying such awful things about him? this is from the same community that preaches about self love and treating others with kindness, and for people who seem to worship a pair of wonderful souls such as Dan and Phil, you really are making fools of yourselves if you’re partaking in this cruelty.

Dan will come back when he’s ready. he hasnt disappeared, he still posts every now and again to show us that he’s still about, still thinking of us. he still interacts with us. some of you really need to remind yourselves what basic human respect is. it wasnt that long ago that Dan opened up about his struggles with mental health, and you still post such insensitive things that he could see at any moment, is that kind?

maybe you need a break from the internet too.

summary: a note on dan and phil:
body:
a note on dan and phil:

i care about these two nerds more than anything. in all seriousness, i am so concerned with their wellbeing. although it is sad that we haven’t gotten a video from dan in months, he’s clearly working on himself and that’s so important. i know we talk about this a lot, but i just wanted to address it again. dan and phil are both such amazing human beings and they deserve all the support we can give them. i genuinely wish nothing but immense happiness for them both. i’m gonna support them through everything.
